Question: Should the government provide free college education to everyone the same way it provides high school education? Explain your answer.
Answer:
I do not think the government should provide free college education the same way it does high school education. The way I look at it, every student should be given the opportunity to attend high school because that should give you the bare minimum you need to know to be a functioning adult. College, on the other hand, should be based on a merit system. If you showed desire to continue your studies and the aptitude to do so, you should be given easy access to a college education.